(161, 1, '2015-09-16 19:37:49', '2015-09-16 19:37:49', '<h3><em>Hidden Creek: The Cure for the Common Community</em></h3>\r\nConstruction on Hidden Creek began this summer. This new community will host 1,000 home sites, a 20-acre park, 142 acres of lakes and homes built by <a href="http://www.beazer.com/houston-TX/bridgeland-hidden-creek---55" target="_blank">Beazer Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.darlinghomes.com/new-homes/texas/houston/cypress/bridgeland-hidden-creek-community" target="_blank">Darling Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.meritagehomes.com/search/houston-tx/bridgeland-hidden-creek/" target="_blank">Meritage Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.perryhomes.com/find-your-home/houston/bridgeland.aspx" target="_blank">Perry Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.ryland.com/find-your-new-home/11-houston/6311-bridgeland.html" target="_blank">Ryland Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.taylormorrison.com/new-homes/texas/houston/cypress/bridgeland-community" target="_blank">Taylor Morrison Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.lennar.com/New-Homes/Texas/Houston/Cypress/Bridgeland/Classic-and-Wentworth-Collections" target="_blank">Village Builders</a> and <a href="http://westin-homes.com/subdivision/bridgeland-sec-6-11/" target="_blank">Westin Homes</a>. New luxury homes range in price from $300,000 to more than $1 million.\r\n\r\nEach neighborhood in Hidden Creek has been named after one of Texas’ noteworthy creek systems.  Additionally, the street names complement a variety of historical and geographical facets of the respective creeks.  Learn more about the meaning behind the names here.\r\n<h3><em>Hidden Creek Amenities</em></h3>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<h4>Lakeland Village Park</h4>\r\n<div>Saving the best for last, the 20-acre Lakeland Village Park boasts a plethora of unique features - offering something for everyone.  The park will include a fenced dog park, a skate park, a basketball court,  a heated lap pool that will be open year-round, a fishing pier, a spray park, as well as multiple tennis courts, playgrounds, walking trails and playfields. The park is expected to be complete by the end of 2015.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<h4>Josey Lake</h4>\r\nThis expansive lake system will stretch for three miles and offer multiple opportunities for active and passive play.  A  canoe and kayak launch will allow residents to paddle for a mile and a half in either direction while enjoying a birding tower and other points of interest along the way.  Stop for a break at Kite Hill, an open play area with spectacular views of Josey Lake.  Many native plants and grasses will line the lake’s edge to provide a natural look and feel for all to enjoy – including the many species of waterfowl that will visit the area!\r\n<h4>Tree House Park</h4>\r\nThis unique play area will offer children an opportunity to play and explore among some of the live oaks that date back to the area’s rice farming days.\r\n\r\n[rev_slider alias="hidden-creek"]', 'Hidden Creek', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hidden-creek', '', '', '2015-09-21 15:45:38', '2015-09-21 15:45:38', '', 155, 'http://bridgeland.jmmcdigitalhosting.com/?page_id=161', 1, 'page', '', 0),
