(434, 1, '2015-02-10 17:47:35', '2015-02-10 17:47:35', 'Back for the eighth year on May 2, Bridgeland’s annual Nature Fest is set to roar into town with a wild combination of exotic creatures, lively activities and tantalizing food trucks. Event attendees will also have the opportunity to see and interact with a rare and respected figure in the wildlife kingdom – Jack Hanna, a long-time animal advocate that has been featured on shows like Good Morning America, The Late Show with David Letterman and other well-known, nationally-syndicated programs.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<span class="caption right media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2484 media-element file-teaser"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/bridgelandnaturefest-200x300jpg"><img class="alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/BridgelandNatureFest-200x300.jpg?itok=h_vs_IxR" alt="BridgelandNatureFest" width="147" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nNature Fest will run from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Saturday, May 2, at Bridgeland’s Oak Meadow Park, 17730 House Hahl Road. Besides attending one of Hanna’s three performances, wild things of all ages are sure enjoy an on-site petting zoo with unique animals like zebras, kangaroos and wallabies, armadillo races, educational reptile and bird shows, as well as many other family-friendly activities.\r\n\r\nDetails about the eighth-annual event are posted online at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/nature-fest">www.bridgeland.com/nature-fest</a>.', 'Bridgeland''s Nature Fest to Feature Performances from Jack Hanna May 2', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bridgelands-nature-fest-to-feature-performances-from-jack-hanna-may-2', '', '', '2015-09-24 18:11:55', '2015-09-24 18:11:55', '', 0, 'http://bridgeland.jmmcdigitalhosting.com/?p=434', 0, 'post', '', 0),
