(454, 1, '2014-10-15 18:57:58', '2014-10-15 18:57:58', 'The Howard Hughes Corp., developer of the Bridgeland community, not only transforms property into award-winning communities, it transforms lives through its charitable contributions. And the corporation has done it again with the donation of a fifth homesite for the Greater Houston Builders Association''s Benefit Homes Project fundraiser. Proceeds from this project will benefit Texas Children''s Cancer Center, the Alzheimer''s Association and HomeAid Houston.<span class="caption none media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2435"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/entrance-2-300x2254jpg"><img class="alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Entrance-2-300x225_4.jpg?itok=lhPOKoLm" alt="Entrance 2" width="220" height="165" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nEach year two homes are built for the Benefit Homes Project with donated land, materials, labor and services. The homes are sold at market value and the majority of the proceeds benefits the three local charities. Since the fundraiser began 34 years ago, $9 million has been raised.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n"We''re proud to provide another homesite for the Benefit Homes Project," said Peter Houghton, Bridgeland''s vice president of master-planned communities. "We''re confident that Bridgeland''s abundant green space, upscale amenities and highly regarded schools will help the Greater Houston Builders Association raise top dollar for Texas Children''s Cancer Center, the Alzheimer''s Association and HomeAid Houston."\r\n\r\nBridgeland, voted the 2013 Master Planned Development of the Year by the GHBA, is an 11,400-acre community that was launched in 2006. The community devotes 3,000 acres to open space and eventually will have a retail component, including a 900-acre town center along Grand Parkway. This community is between U.S. 290 and I-10 on Fry Road and is bisected by a segment of Grand Parkway.\r\n\r\nManaged by The Woodlands Development Co., Bridgeland and The Woodlands share the same development philosophy and benefit from The Woodlands'' 40 years of successful real estate development. Both communities have been listed among the top-selling master-planned communities in Texas and the nation and offer a variety of housing options, extensive outdoor recreation and a focus on environmental preservation. Both master-planned communities are projects of The Howard Hughes Corp., which owns, manages and develops commercial, residential and mixed-used real estate throughout the U.S.\r\n\r\nAdditional development has begun on 450 acres within the Hidden Creek neighborhood. Hidden Creek currently is the largest neighborhood in Bridgeland and offers 1,000 homesites.\r\n\r\nNew luxury homes are expected to range in price from $280,000 to over $1 million. Lakeland Heights, one of Bridgeland''s other neighborhoods under development, will offer 200 new homesites and four additional product lines.\r\n\r\n"Thankfully we are in the greater Houston region, and we are blessed with a robust economy," said Tim Welbes, co-president of The Woodlands Development Co. "It is especially important that from time to time we pause for a special event/project like the GHBA Benefit Homes Project. We are honored to be able to participate and look forward to supporting the very deserving beneficiaries."', 'Bridgeland Donates Fifth Homesite to Benefit Home Project', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bridgeland-donates-fifth-homesite-to-benefit-home-project', '', '', '2015-09-28 21:27:30', '2015-09-28 21:27:30', '', 0, 'http://bridgeland.jmmcdigitalhosting.com/?p=454', 0, 'post', '', 0),
