(505, 1, '2014-03-06 20:09:09', '2014-03-06 20:09:09', '<a href="http://www.howardhughes.com/">The Howard Hughes Corporation</a>® (NYSE: HHC) announced today that additional development will immediately commence at its award winning <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">Bridgeland </a>master planned community (MPC) located in the fast-growing northwest Houston area. In late February the MPC received a permit from the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers to develop 806 acres within the Hidden Creek neighborhood. The announcement is expected to spur significant interest as homebuyers are attracted to Bridgeland for its improving transportation options, wide range of upscale housing and well-regarded schools. Bridgeland was also deemed the 2013 ‘Master Planned Development of the Year’ by the Greater Houston Builders Association (GHBA), just one of more than 100 accolades the community has received.\r\n\r\n“As northwest Houston continues to experience unprecedented growth, the community, home builders, real estate agents and interested residents have all anxiously awaited the announcement of Hidden Creek,” said Paul Layne, Executive Vice President of Master Planned Communities for The Howard Hughes Corporation. “We are moving ahead with this exceptional neighborhood that will epitomize the Bridgeland lifestyle by bringing together luxury homes surrounded by lakes, parks and other amenities that create a distinct lifestyle for our residents.”\r\n\r\nAs the largest neighborhood to be built in Bridgeland to date, Hidden Creek will boast 1,000 homesites surrounded by 142 acres of lakes and waterways. Lots will be delivered in mid-2014 to some of Houston’s most respected builders. New luxury homes are expected to range in price from $200,000 to over $1 million. Lakeland Heights, one of Bridgeland’s other neighborhoods under development, will also offer 200 new homesites and four additional product lines.\r\n\r\nHidden Creek will introduce an extensive array of amenities, including Lakeland Village Park, a 20-acre green space that will feature an enclosed dog park, a basketball court, canoe launch and a skate park. Additional tennis courts, picnic areas, walking trails and pavilions are also planned as well as a splash pad, playground and year-round heated lap pool. Josey Lake, an expansive waterway that runs along the perimeter of Hidden Creek, will enable residents to canoe three miles from end to end or stop and explore the birding tower and boardwalk along the way.\r\n\r\nCommitted to preserving nature in the community, Bridgeland has dedicated more than 3,000 acres to lakes, trails and parks within the 11,400-acre master planned community. Aside from Lakeland Village Park, Hidden Creek will also have three smaller multi-use green spaces, including a park with a large tree house, which will allow children to play among live oaks that date back to the property’s early rice farming days. Similar to other sections of the community, an extensive trail system will be located within Hidden Creek, including a bike trail that will eventually lead to Bridgeland’s Town Center, which will offer residents popular dining, shopping and entertainment choices.\r\n\r\nFor more information on Bridgeland, a wholly-owned subsidiary of <a href="https://now.howardhughes.com/">The Howard Hughes Corporation</a> and managed by<a href="http://www.thewoodlands.com/">The Woodlands</a>, visit <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>, <a href="http://www.facebook.com/Bridgelandcommunity">Facebook</a> or <a href="http://www.twitter.com/BridgelandTweet">Twitter</a>.', 'Construction Starts on Highly Anticipated Hidden Creek Neighborhood in Bridgeland', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'construction-starts-on-highly-anticipated-hidden-creek-neighborhood-in-bridgeland', '', '', '2015-09-24 20:09:41', '2015-09-24 20:09:41', '', 0, 'http://bridgeland.jmmcdigitalhosting.com/?p=505', 0, 'post', '', 0),
